feedback:
Some of the faces were a bit off-putting and creepy. ONE of them was so creepy that it seemed to have been excavated from a shadowy crevasse at the heart of the Uncanny Valley.
The strange and surprising thing is that I found myself more trusting and receptive to the face that looked entirely like a robot than I was of the slightly-more-human-looking faces. The chrome-faced guy was more endearing than creepy. But it wasn't sporting a perverse simulacrum of a human smile, so that might account for the difference.
